{"body": "I'm :+1: for this feature, being able to specify types of indexes is nice definitely better than having to go in and write it manually: \n\n```\n  def up\n    execute \"CREATE INDEX products_gin_data ON products USING GIN(data)\"\n  end\n\n  def down\n    execute \"DROP INDEX products_gin_data\"\n  end\n```\n\nI made a comment on code style, do you think you could fix that up, rebase this code, and we can get someone from ActiveRecord to take a look?\n", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/8839227", "created_at": "2012-09-24T23:51:46Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/6101#issuecomment-8839227", "updated_at": "2012-09-24T23:51:46Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 6101, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/schneems", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/db953d125f5cc49756edb6149f1b813e?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F6ef42a6eab211ddd71ac423a80b42d15.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/received_events", "gravatar_id": "db953d125f5cc49756edb6149f1b813e", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "schneems", "type": "User", "id": 59744, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/schneems/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52380dc2bd3543c15100d33e"}, "id": 8839227, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/6101"}
